# Date Handling Fix Plan

## Goal Description
The user reported that "Perfect Days" and habit history are not verifying/updating correctly. 
The root cause is the use of `new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]`, which returns the UTC date. In Korea (UTC+9), this means that between 00:00 and 09:00 AM, the app records actions as happening on the *previous* day.
This change ensures the app always uses the device's **Local Time** for dates.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This fix changes how "Today" is calculated. It will use the local device time. If a user travels across timezones, "Today" will shift accordingly. This is generally the expected behavior for a personal habit tracker.

